Name: add_frame
Comment: Add a frame with the name name initialized at the specified pose expressed in the ref_name coordinate frame.

Parameters.Label: name
Parameters.Comment: name of the frame to be added. The name must not be the same as any existing world model object (frame, axis, or axis group), otherwise an exception is thrown

Parameters.Label: pose
Parameters.Comment: initial pose of the new frame

Parameters.Label: refname
Parameters.Comment: name of the world model object whose coordinate frame the pose is expressed in. If nothing is provided here, the default is the robot's "base" frame.

Name: attach_frame
Comment: Attaches the child frame to the parent world model object.

Parameters.Label: child
Parameters.Comment: name of the frame to be attached. The name must not be \“world\”, \“flange\”, or \“tcp\”.

Parameters.Label: parent
Parameters.Comment: name of the object that the child frame will be attached to

Name: delete_all_frames
Comment: Delete all frames that have been added to the world model.

Name: delete_frame
Comment: Delete the named frame from the world model.

Parameters.Label: name
Parameters.Comment: name of the frame to be deleted

Name: move_frame
Comment: Changes the placement of the coordinate frame named name to the new placement given by pose that is defined in the ref_name coordinate frame.

Parameters.Label: name
Parameters.Comment: name of the frame to be moved. The name must not be the same as any existing world model object (frame, axis, or axis group), otherwise an exception is thrown

Parameters.Label: pose
Parameters.Comment: the new placement

Parameters.Label: refname
Parameters.Comment: name of the coordinate frame that the pose is expressed in. If nothing is provided here, the default is the robot's "base" frame.

Name: get_pose
Comment: Get the pose of the name frame relative to the rel_name frame but expressed in the coordinates of the ref_name frame.

Parameters.Label: name
Parameters.Comment: name of the frame to query.

Parameters.Label: rel_name
Parameters.Comment: short for “relative frame name” is the frame where the pose is computed relative to

Parameters.Label: ref_name
Parameters.Comment: short for “reference frame name” is the frame to express the coordinates of resulting relative pose in. If this is not provided, then it will default to match the value of rel_name.

Parameters.Label: pose
Parameters.Comment: pose to be converted.

Parameters.Label: from_frame
Parameters.Comment: name of reference frame at origin of old coordinate system

Parameters.Label: to_frame
Parameters.Comment: name of reference frame at origin of new coordinate system.

Name: reset_world_model
Comment: Delete all frames, axis groups, and axes that were added to the world model. This also moves the robot’s base to the world origin.

Name: is_frame
Return: true if there is a frame by the given name, false if not.
Comment: Queries for the existence of a frame by the given name.

Parameters.Label: name
Parameters.Comment: name of the frame to be queried

Name: get_frame_parent
Return: name of the parent as a string
Comment: Get the parent of the frame named name in the world model.

Parameters.Label: name
Parameters.Comment: name of the frame to be queried

Name: get_children
Return: array strings : the names of the children of the queried frame
Comment: Returns a list of immediate child object frame names.

Parameters.Label: name
Parameters.Comment: the name of the parent object.

Parameters.Label: frame_name
Parameters.Comment: Name of the frame in the world model to track. This can also be the name of an axis added with the 'axis_group_add_axis()' command.

Name: set_mass_properties
Comment: Set mass properties (including mass m, center of gravity cog, and inertia matrix inertia) of the frame.

Parameters.Label: m
Parameters.Comment: mass in kg

Parameters.Label: cog
Parameters.Comment: Center of Gravity: an array with three elements [CoGx, CoGy, CoGz] specifying the offset (in meters) from the frame origin.

Parameters.Label: inertia
Parameters.Comment: Inertia: an array with six elements [Ixx, Iyy, Izz, Ixy, Ixz, Iyz] with origin in the CoG and the axes aligned with the frame axes

Name: set_payload_from_attached_frames
Comment: Set the payload based on the attached frames. This will compute the effective mass and inertia from frames on an attachment chain to the TCP and set it as the payload.
